2. Interpretation
In these regulations-
"certificate holder" has the same meaning assigned to it under the Act;
"Director" has the same meaning assigned to it under the Act;
"industrial licence" has the same meaning assigned to it under the Act;
"licensee" has the same meaning assigned to it under the Act;
"manufacturing enterprise" has the same meaning assigned to it under the Act;
"micro manufacturing enterprise" means a business entity as defined under regulation 10(1)( a );
"registration certificate" has the same meaning assigned to it under the Act;
"small manufacturing enterprise" means a business entity as defined under regulation 10(1)( b ) ; and
"the Act" means the Industrial Development Act.

3. Industrial licences reserved for citizens
An industrial licence to operate any of the following manufacturing enterprises shall be reserved for citizens in terms of section 5(5)( a ) of the Act-
( a ) bread and confectionery;
( b ) ice making;
( c ) meat processing;
( d ) peanut butter;
( e ) purification and bottling of water;
( f ) traditional sour milk; and
( g ) sorghum.

11. Registration certificates reserved for citizens
A registration certificate to operate any of the following manufacturing enterprises shall be reserved for citizens in terms of section 16(2)( a ) of the Act-
( a ) bricks;
( b ) burglar bars, gates and windows;
( c ) candles;
( d ) fencing materials excluding gum poles;
( e ) floor polish;
( f ) packaging;
( g ) protective clothing;
( h ) roof trusses;
( i ) school furniture;
( j ) school uniforms;
( k ) screen printing and embroidery;
( l ) signage, including electronic signage;
( m ) traditional crafts; and
(n) traditional leather products.
